caption: New owners and food are absolutely amazing. Food is superb and authentic! 10/10
The spring rolls was hot and great. My pad cashew was delicious and the peanut tofu my cousin said was great...

I’d give this place a solid four stars based on a good half a dozen experiences. The quality of the food’s always been very decent but where were missing the fifth star is a combination of level of service when dining in, accuracy of orders when ordering take-out, and the restaurant itself which is a tad, and I mean just a tad, tun down.
Ruang Khao Thai Cuisine was exactly what I was looking for. The food is scrumptious and the staff is above and beyond. I highly recommend this restaurant!
Gave this place another try under new management. Ordered two appetizers and three entrees. All were very good, delicious. Will definitely be back. The crab fried rice is especially good.
This place is pretty good, I had them deliver food to me and I enjoyed it. I had the Tom Kha soup and spicy eggplant, and really loved the soup!

I ordered the panang curry with beef, and it was very tasty. The peanuts were ground up into the sauce which was nice. Staff was friendly when I went in to pick it up, and they mentioned that free delivery is an option.

I celebrated my PhD this evening in this great place. happy to tell that it was a great evening and the restaurant was unquestionably one of the reasons for that happy gathering. The team  contributed in a graceful manner, the cooking was yummy and my friends were very  joyful. We shall absolutely visit again for more joyful events. Thank you very much.

They delivered food pretty fast eventhough it was snowing and it was free of charge! I ordered Pad Thai and Panang curry and they were tasty. I'd go back next time to support them again. Good thai restaurant in the area for sure!

I ordered a carry out order yesterday and I was pleasantly surprised to see that the restaurant is remodeling inside. I am excited to dine in when they open back up. I ordered the drunken noodle and it was very tasty and nicely cooked, I also had the tom kha soup which I will get every time because it was so good. I may try the pad thai next time. The hostess was very polite which was a change from before, and told me that they deliver for free now if you just call to order, or do it on the restaurant website.

We love to go out. Last night we  found this superb place which we didn’t know before. We spent a beautiful evening there with exceptional meal and  an experienced team and a distinguished chief cook. We put this venue in our list  and we will surely go again soon. We highly recommend.
Delicious, authentic Thai food, I really enjoyed it!
This spot is wonderful and broad, the meals was delightful and the rates were very reasonable. quickly, productive service and very amiable staff members. I recommend this place.
First time ordering from Ruang Khao, and everything was exceptional. I think I've found my new go-to for Thai!
Customer service was very poor and they have improve on their foof. Very tastless?

This place is no doubt one of the best restaurants in the neighborhood. Every time I come to this place I am so pleased. They manage their high  level service and the topmost level of cooking  they provide. You definitely will enjoy this this restaurant. Warmly  recommended.
Great food, kind employees, constantly good character. They charge fair prices and the food quality is good. Keep it up.
Oh my god the food is so tasty. Best Thai in silver spring. Worth the slight walk out of downtown.
If there is a no star or negative, I would definitely choose it. The food is not that much good and the services is horrible. The host is very disrespectful. I will never ever be back to this place.

I’ve been eating here for about two years now and I really love it every single time. I get the drunken noodles with lo mein instead of flat noodles and it’s so good. I wish there were more delivery options but it’s worth going all the way there for the Thai iced tea
The Food was soooooo delicious
I ordered the fried rice kaprow. Child it was semi burnt. Smh. The customer service was ok and the speed was good. I'll try again but the food better be on point.

I admire this restaurant! They offer delicious meals, their menu is rich, The cook in that spot is a specialist, I enjoy very much tasting all their dishes. The food is always good, the service towards the clients  is good. I often go to  this restaurant and I not even once was unsatisfied. I recommend it with no hesitation.

We enjoy hanging out. Yesterday we arrived in this excellent restaurant which friends recommended to us. We passed a delightful time there with delicious food and a well-trained crew and  a professional  chef. We  added this fine restaurant in our list  and we shall no doubt come back soon. We warmly recommend.

Ordered from Uber Eats. Two of three dishes ordered were less than satisfactory. Mangoes in sticky rice were brown and rancid. No one should serve fruit that looks this way. Pumpkin was hard and under cooked. When I called to inquire, the person who answered was rude and defensive about their food. There is no pride taken with the food or customer service. There are so many other Thai choices in Silver Spring where you can spend your money and be respected.
My daughter found a hair in her dumplings.

I don’t usually write reviews but I decided I had to write one because every time I’ve ordered something it’s been great. I wanted to take a pick of the pad Thai I ordered but I scarfed most of it down before I decided to stop and leave a comment.... some might say that pad Thai so simple it’s hard to mess up... and yet other Thai restaurants in the neighborhood manage to do so. Ruan is not the best in the area it’s one of the best in the DMV.  I at least took a pic of the curry puffs I got (also as a carry out). They’re full of flavor slightly heavy on the curry but still great. The puffs and cucumber sauce are still the best from any restaurant I’ve been to.
Great Thai food, great service!
Best Thai food in Silver Spring. Fresh, spicy, and interesting flavors.
Great Thai food. Staff were very on top of refills and service.

I just ordered UBER EATS from this place and they delivered the food.. rice and curry in sauce.. WITH NO FORK OR SPOON!.  When I called the restaurant to complain they blamed ME?  WTH?  I'll NEVER order from these people again and I'm telling 10 friends to never order here again either.  They SUCK
Incredible food and great little lunch getaway spot.  Loved it, can't wait to go back.
Good lunch area. Customer service not so great
The best pad Thai I’ve ever had... get it with shrimp!

This place is super good. Word of warning!!! Do not ask for thai level spice unless you are ready for it. I got the southern curry special and mentioned I had visited Thailand and was okay with the spice level. What I brought home was an absolute scorcher. It was great though - still had flavor with the heat. The shrimp spring rolls are also great.

This is a favorite local spot for us in Silver Spring.  Vera is so nice and her service is exceptional.  Out of all the Thai food places in the area this is hands down our favorite.  The smaller atmosphere and usually not overly packed dining area we really enjoy.  Placing pick-up orders is extremely easy by phone but I know several delivery services including Grubhub offer online ordering.

This restaurant is reason why every man, woman and child whould learn how to cook and stay home. There is no redeeming value in this place, the people or their food. It is clear in tasting their food that the owners have no self repsct. Please order at your own cost.

Delicious Thai dishes,friendly staffs and beautiful decoration. Their lunch special is the best deal in town, no one can beat them. I love papaya salad, Lad Nah pak, drunken noodles, Deep fried shrimps and many more..
Really enjoyed the curry!

Review for delivery - Panang Curry with tofu was tasty and there was a ton of tofu in the meal, although I wish more veggies were incorporated. The fresh rolls are a disappointment, though. Mostly lettuce and just one small shrimp in each roll. I’m used to fresh rolls with substantially more protein and less filler.
Very good.

great food and service. the portions are large if you get the lunch special.... I had the drunken noodles and they had like 0.5 spicy level and it was great... the spring rules were really good and the atmosphere was really good.not lots of people except many people from the region.... best thai fold I have had yet... old converted house

I go to two Thai restaurants in the area. This one and Kin Da in Takoma Park. The food has always been outstanding and service is quick and friendly. And as a long time vegetarian, I love the multitude of options. My teenage son and husband also love this place. Everyone is happy to eat here!
We waited two hours for delivery. The food looked and tasted like last week's leftovers.
Love the food here nice service also.
Amazing food. Some of the best thai food I've had in a long time. Pineapple fried rice is on point. Taro rotti/coconut ice cream
Great food! Great service!
Small, quiet place with good food and decent service
Good food, like the menu. Unbeatable price.

I often walk by the outdoor patio here, which is shady and inviting by early evening in the summer  Service was a bit confused though. Our server didn't know the beers they carried and they didn't have a drink menu. She also told us that they had no wine, yet 15 minutes later a person at the next table was served a glass. We liked the spring rolls but our curries were unremarkable.

Tasty vegetarian / vegan fare. Sweet & mellow wooden deck for outdoor dining. Reasonable prices. On same block as Urban Winery and Quarry House Tavern (great beer and whisky selections!). Worth a visit, particularly on a lovely day!
We love the Pad Prik King. Also had pumpkin curry which is milder.
Great food, so tasty

Full menu.  Great options. Tom Yum very nice.  Pumpkin Spice curry quite tasty. They have a spicy scale of 1 - 5.  I like spicy.  More than the average American.  I asked for #4. It was right at the edge of tolerable.  Glad I didn't go for a 5. (And the spice did not overpower the flavour.)
Great crab fried rice
Nice lunch specials
Good food
Good prices, fast service, and good food
Very good food, though server had difficulty using register
Food was average and the service was not the best, they forgot a lot of items ordered and rushed us out of the restaurant. Could have been better Thai food overall.
Price is really right. Food is really good.

If there is a no star, I would definitely choose it.  This place has the worst customer service ever! We ordered 2 Drunkun Noddles (Kee Mao) and the noddles were OVERCOOKED. Very soggy and soft. The noddles are supposed to be soft but still has its texture. The waiter and chef were not willing to redo the dish, but kept asking what is weong with it! The food was not edible and I will not come back and will not recommend to others.
Order through Uber Eats and was very disappointed with the quality of food. Will not eat here again.
Awful food now. Used to be five stars. Guess they're failing because they have changed the beef and chicken they use. So gross.
We loved it. Went on a Saturday night and had the outdoor patio to ourselves. Food was tastey -- noyh vegetarian versions of a curry and basil dish. Lovely wait staff person.
Been here many times and the food is wonderful. Simple and good.
food is delicious, kids love it, I love it. This place never disappoints.
This is reincarnation of the famous Thai Derm. Updated decor inside while I am missing the old one. An addition of a patio for about 5 tables. Fast service, Good testing food.
had take out and it was delicious.
It's testy fresh food & friendly customer service.
Nice and friendly environment. Food is fresh and prepared by family members. They have some nice specials. Good all around and almost a hidden gem and sleeper if you ask me.
Pad thai and green curry were great!

If i could give them a negative score I would!! Terrible food, terrible customer service, especially terrible delivery driver!! If you have a problem with your order don't expect them to resolve it without you having to provide a lengthy dissertation on why you're unhappy. Customers beware!!!
Tasty curries.  Disappointing fish with 3 flavor sauce (there was very little sauce and the fish was overcooked).  The pad Thai was made with tomato instead of tamarind.
